    "body": "the helper function [__Pyx_PyNumber_IntOrLong](https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/master/Cython/Utility/TypeConversion.c#L268) explicitly raises a ``TypeError``, i.e. on lines 306, 313. However, if ``CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS`` is not used, it calls directly to ``PyNumber_Int`` in line 298. The error will not be recast by the code on line 314. \r\n\r\nIf ``PyNumber_Int`` fails, it raises a ``ValueError``, not a ``TypeError``, so downstream users must catch both errors on platforms like PyPy where ``CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS`` is not defined.\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "body": "This patch fixes the issue for PyPy at the cost of always running ``PyErr_Clear``\r\n\r\n``` diff \r\n--- a/Cython/Utility/Coroutine.c\r\n+++ b/Cython/Utility/Coroutine.c\r\n@@ -310,10 +310,10 @@ static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyNumber_IntOrLong(PyObject* x) {\r\n       return NULL;\r\n     }\r\n   }\r\n-  else if (!PyErr_Occurred()) {\r\n-    PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,\r\n+  PyErr_Clear();\r\n+  if (!res)\r\n+  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,\r\n                     \"an integer is required\");\r\n-  }\r\n   return res;\r\n }\r\n``` \r\n",
            "created_at": "2017-05-12T13:21:20Z",
